  "body": "As part of our move towards c++20, we need to remove all instances of `using namespace std;` usage in order to alleviate current and future name clashes from within different namespaces; a prominent example of this is our use of `ranges`, where we are currently using `rangesv3` and will switch to `std::ranges`.\r\n\r\nThis is also a prerequisite for the introduction of `clang-format`, which should make our style checking and consistency of said style significantly easier.\r\n\r\nThe following directories are to be adapted:\r\n\r\n- [x] libevmasm\r\n- [ ] liblangutil\r\n- [ ] libsmtutil\r\n- [ ] libsolc\r\n- [ ] libsolidity/analysis\r\n- [ ] libsolidity/ast\r\n- [ ] libsolidity/codegen\r\n- [ ] libsolidity/formal\r\n- [ ] libsolidity/interface\r\n- [ ] libsolidity/lsp\r\n- [ ] libsolidity/parsing\r\n- [ ] libsolutil\r\n- [ ] libyul\r\n- [ ] libyul/backend\r\n- [ ] libyul/optimiser\r\n- [ ] solc",
